// Fig. 9 — Who actually grew? Cumulative % growth by region, 1901–2011.
// Purpose: the top of the chart is West India (Gujarat + Maharashtra) at
// ~507%, not the Hindi belt. The Hindi belt sits second at ~411%, barely
// above the national average of 408%. The South — the supposed paragon of
// restraint — is at the bottom at ~335%, but that figure hides the fact
// that the South grew *fastest* in the first half of the century and only
// slowed from the 1970s onward.
---

