  <figcaption class="fig-head">
    <span class="fig-label">Fig. 9</span>
    <span class="fig-title">Who actually grew?</span>
    <span class="fig-unit">— cumulative % growth, 1901 → 2011 —</span>
  </figcaption>
  <div id="cumulative-chart" class="chart cumulative-chart"></div>
  <p class="fig-note">
    <span class="hi">कुल वृद्धि, क्षेत्र-वार</span> ·
    The dashed vermilion line is the national average (~408%). The <b>West</b>
    — Gujarat &amp; Maharashtra — outgrew every other region, not the Hindi
    belt. The <b>South</b>'s aggregate growth is the lowest of the four
    <em>only when the whole century is flattened</em>; from 1901 to 1951 it
    actually grew faster than the North.
  </p>
